{"title_page": "Acnistus", "text_new": "{{Italic title}}{{taxobox\n|name = ''Acnistus''\n|image = Acnistus arborescens 1.jpg\n|image_caption = ''[[Acnistus arborescens]]''\n|regnum = [[Plantae]]\n|unranked_divisio = [[Angiosperms]]\n|unranked_classis = [[Eudicots]]\n|unranked_ordo = [[Asterids]]\n|ordo = [[Solanales]]\n|familia = [[Solanaceae]]\n|subfamilia = Solanoideae\n|tribus = Physaleae\n|genus = '''''Acnistus'''''\n|genus_authority = [[Heinrich Wilhelm Schott|Schott]]\n|subdivision_ranks = [[Species]]\n|subdivision = See text\n|}}\n\n'''''N.B.''''' the monotypic genus Acnistus was subsumed in the genus [[Iochroma]] by J.M.H. Shaw in 2016 and the species formerly known as ''Acnistus arborescens'' is now known correctly as '''''Iochroma arborescens (L.) J.M.H.  Shaw'''''  ].<ref>Shaw, J. M. H. 2016. (2434) Proposal to conserve Iochroma nom. cons. (Solanaceae) against the additional names Acnistus and Pederlea. Taxon 65: 395\u2013396.</ref><ref>http://www.plantsoftheworldonline.org/taxon/urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:77186334-1 Retrieved at 11.07am on 28/4/19</ref>\n\n'''''Acnistus''''' is a monotypic genus in the plant family [[Solanaceae]], the nightshade family : the only species currently recognised is ''[[Acnistus arborescens]]'' - common names ( inter alia ) ''Hollowheart'',  ''Fruta de sabi\u00e1''.<ref> Armando T. Hunziker: ''The Genera of Solanaceae''. A.R.G. Gantner Verlag K.G., Ruggell, Liechtenstein 2001. {{ISBN|3-904144-77-4}} pps. 199-202.</ref><ref  name=usfs>Francis, J. K. [http://www.fs.fd.us/global/iitf/pdf/shrubs/Acnistus%20arborescens.pdf ''Acnistus arborescens''.] USDA Forest Service, International Institute of Tropical Forestry, Jard\u00edn Bot\u00e1nico Sur, Puerto Rico.</ref> This species has recently been transferred to '''''Iochroma''''' <ref>http://plantsoftheworldonline.org/taxon/urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:77186334-1</ref>. \n\n*''[[Acnistus cauliflorus]]'' is a synonym of '' Acnistus arborescens''\n*''[[Acnistus lorentzii]]'' is an unresolved name, but some data suggest that it is synonymous with Eriolarynx lorentzii (Dammer) Hunz. \n*''[[Acnistus parviflorus]]'' is a synonym of ''Acnistus arborescens''\n<ref>Acnistus arborescens The Plant List http://www.theplantlist.org/tpl1.1/record/kew-2618239 retrieved 10.52 a.m. 14/2/19</ref>\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q2706011}}\n\n[[Category:Physaleae]]\n[[Category:Solanaceae genera]]\n\n\n{{Solanales-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Italic title}}{{taxobox\n|name = ''Acnistus''\n|image = Acnistus arborescens 1.jpg\n|image_caption = ''[[Acnistus arborescens]]''\n|regnum = [[Plantae]]\n|unranked_divisio = [[Angiosperms]]\n|unranked_classis = [[Eudicots]]\n|unranked_ordo = [[Asterids]]\n|ordo = [[Solanales]]\n|familia = [[Solanaceae]]\n|subfamilia = Solanoideae\n|tribus = Physaleae\n|genus = '''''Acnistus'''''\n|genus_authority = [[Heinrich Wilhelm Schott|Schott]]\n|subdivision_ranks = [[Species]]\n|subdivision = See text\n|}}\n\n[ '''''N.B.''''' the monotypic genus Acnistus was subsumed in the genus [[Iochroma]] by J.M.H. Shaw in 2016 and the species formerly known as ''Acnistus arborescens'' is now known correctly as '''''Iochroma arborescens (L.) J.M.H.  Shaw'''''  ].<ref>Shaw, J. M. H. 2016. (2434) Proposal to conserve Iochroma nom. cons. (Solanaceae) against the additional names Acnistus and Pederlea. Taxon 65: 395\u2013396.</ref><ref>http://www.plantsoftheworldonline.org/taxon/urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:77186334-1 Retrieved at 11.07am on 28/4/19</ref>\n\n'''''Acnistus''''' is a monotypic genus in the plant family [[Solanaceae]], the nightshade family : the only species currently recognised is ''[[Acnistus arborescens]]'' - common names ( inter alia ) ''Hollowheart'',  ''Fruta de sabi\u00e1''.<ref> Armando T. Hunziker: ''The Genera of Solanaceae''. A.R.G. Gantner Verlag K.G., Ruggell, Liechtenstein 2001. {{ISBN|3-904144-77-4}} pps. 199-202.</ref><ref  name=usfs>Francis, J. K. [http://www.fs.fd.us/global/iitf/pdf/shrubs/Acnistus%20arborescens.pdf ''Acnistus arborescens''.] USDA Forest Service, International Institute of Tropical Forestry, Jard\u00edn Bot\u00e1nico Sur, Puerto Rico.</ref> This species has recently been transferred to '''''Iochroma''''' <ref>http://plantsoftheworldonline.org/taxon/urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:77186334-1</ref>. \n\n*''[[Acnistus cauliflorus]]'' is a synonym of '' Acnistus arborescens''\n*''[[Acnistus lorentzii]]'' is an unresolved name, but some data suggest that it is synonymous with Eriolarynx lorentzii (Dammer) Hunz. \n*''[[Acnistus parviflorus]]'' is a synonym of ''Acnistus arborescens''\n<ref>Acnistus arborescens The Plant List http://www.theplantlist.org/tpl1.1/record/kew-2618239 retrieved 10.52 a.m. 14/2/19</ref>\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q2706011}}\n\n[[Category:Physaleae]]\n[[Category:Solanaceae genera]]\n\n\n{{Solanales-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Nuzaliwaj", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acnistus"}
{"title_page": "International cricket in 1970", "text_new": "{{International cricket years|1969\u201370|1970\u201371}}\n\nThe 1970 International cricket season was from May 1970 to September 1970.<ref>{{cite web|title=Season 1970|url=http://static.espncricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/1970S/1970/|website=ESPNcricinfo|accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref> However, there were no any international match held during this season. The season consisted with [[1970 English cricket season]] where they held [[1970 County Championship]] from 25 July to 25 August, [[1970 Gillette Cup]] and [[1970 John Player League]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Season 1970 overview|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/series/index.html?season=1970;view=season|website=ESPNcricinfo|accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref> However, Rest of the World XI toured England for an unofficial Test series. At the time, they were played as [[Test cricket|Test matches]], but that status was later revoked by the [[International Cricket Conference]] (ICC) and they are now termed unofficial Tests, though still officially [[first-class cricket|first-class matches]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/magazine/content/story/149171.html |title=Golden gloves |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=7 November 2018}}</ref>\n{{TOC right|limit=2}}\n\n==Season overview==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"7\" |International tours\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Start date\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Home team\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Away team\n! colspan=\"4\" |Results [Matches]\n|-\n![[Test cricket|Test]]\n![[One Day International|ODI]]\n![[First class cricket|FC]]\n![[List A cricket|LA]]\n|-\n|[[#World XI in England|{{dts|3 June 1971}}]]\n|{{Cr|ENG}}\n|[[World XI (cricket)|World XI]]\n|; style=\"text-align:center\"| \u2014\n|; style=\"text-align:center\"| \u2014\n|1\u20134 [6]\n|; style=\"text-align:center\"| \u2014\n|}\n\n==June==\n=== World XI in England ===\n{{main|Rest of the World cricket team in England in 1970}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! colspan=\